Alright, from the search results, it seems there are several techniques researchers use to minimize this bias. One of them is using indirect questioning methods, like the randomized response technique, where respondents' answers are probabilistically determined, ensuring privacy.

Another method is the forced-choice method, where respondents choose between two or more options, making it harder to pick the socially desirable answer all the time. Also, the third-person technique, where respondents are asked to think about how others might behave instead of themselves, can sometimes reduce bias.

